<li id="cite_note-11"><b><a href="#cite_ref-11" title="">^</a></b> "<cite>Borrowing from Charles Darwin's theory of evolution, social Darwinists believed that societies, as do organisms evolve over time. Nature then determined that the strong survive and the weak perish. In Jack London's case, he thought that certain favored races were destined for survival, mainly those that could preserve themselves while supplanting others, as in the case of the White race.</cite>" <a href="http://sunsite.berkeley.edu/London/Essays/philosophy.html" class="external text" title="http://sunsite.berkeley.edu/London/Essays/philosophy.html" rel="nofollow">The philosophy of Jack London</a></li>
